kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
Clouds floating above the surface</i>

26
00:01:17,321 --> 00:01:22,160
<i>I am open from midnight to seven of the morning after.
kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
Clouds floating above the surface</i>

27
00:01:22,970 --> 00:01:23,915
<i>People call this...</i>

28
00:01:24,045 --> 00:01:26,557
<i>Midnight Restaurant.</i>

29
00:01:27,060 --> 00:01:28,476
<i>How is business doing?!</i>

30
00:01:29,242 --> 00:01:31,471
<i>Well enough, I'd say.</i>

31
00:01:31,734 --> 00:01:34,654
~ SHINYA SHOKUDO ~
Midnight Restaurant

32
00:01:34,654 --> 00:01:40,246
Episode 7
Egg Sandwich

33
00:01:44,170 --> 00:01:46,201
<i>If you tell me anything you'd like,</i>

34
00:01:46,226 --> 00:01:48,046
<i>I'll make it for you if possible.</i>

35
00:01:54,109 --> 00:01:55,154
I guess...

36
00:01:55,179 --> 00:01:56,962
traditional tonjiru will do.

37
00:01:58,413 --> 00:01:59,853
Coming.

38
00:02:02,147 --> 00:02:03,775
Can I shoot a photo?

39
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:05,420
I want to post it on my blog.

40
00:02:05,630 --> 00:02:06,600
Blog?!

41
00:02:06,732 --> 00:02:08,892
It's a kind of diary
you write on your PC.

42
00:02:09,069 --> 00:02:10,559
Have no problem with that,

43
00:02:10,710 --> 00:02:13,540
but make sure you
don't promote this place.

44
00:02:14,709 --> 00:02:16,079
That's weird.

45
00:02:16,449 --> 00:02:18,109
Uh? Why?

46
00:02:18,443 --> 00:02:21,988
Most people actually ask me
for a photo, to get some publicity.

47
00:02:22,013 --> 00:02:24,133
Is that so?

48
00:02:26,253 --> 00:02:28,403
Here you go.

49
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:33,343
<i>(*TV actress)</i>
I'm aspiring to become a talent*.

50
00:02:33,368 --> 00:02:36,588
Although I'm probably busier
working part time at our family restaurant.

51
00:02:36,716 --> 00:02:39,406
I see...
So that's why you blog...

52
00:02:40,386 --> 00:02:43,136
If I can get even just
a little bit of publicity....

53
00:02:46,510 --> 00:02:49,470
Seems like he'll be here soon.

54
00:02:54,353 --> 00:02:55,223
Good morning.

55
00:02:55,356 --> 00:02:56,785
Morning.

56
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:58,820
Can you make me an egg sandwich?

57
00:03:17,416 --> 00:03:20,626
I also made you ones with
cucumber and ham.

58
00:03:20,651 --> 00:03:22,361
Thank you.

59
00:03:39,947 --> 00:03:41,477
If you'd like to, go ahead.

60
00:03:41,502 --> 00:03:42,440
Uh?!

61
00:03:43,540 --> 00:03:45,380
May I?

62
00:03:45,968 --> 00:03:47,558
Thank you.

63
00:03:58,420 --> 00:04:00,110
Is something on my face?

64
00:04:00,189 --> 00:04:01,269
No...

65
00:04:02,140 --> 00:04:05,790
Just seemed like you were enjoying it.

66
00:04:11,263 --> 00:04:13,583
Are there any decent
men left out there?!

67
00:04:13,673 --> 00:04:14,993
It was a disaster.

68
00:04:15,133 --> 00:04:17,763
We should have just
remained at home watching TV.

69
00:04:17,826 --> 00:04:19,846
Those ads were just a farce.

70
00:04:20,479 --> 00:04:22,349
What could it be?

71
00:04:22,630 --> 00:04:26,090
They went to, what is it,
an omiai party or something?

72
00:04:26,233 --> 00:04:29,453
Here. Beer and macaroni salad.

73
00:04:29,557 --> 00:04:30,397
Master.

74
00:04:30,439 --> 00:04:32,839
Didn't one of them
go back to her hometown?

75
00:04:33,723 --> 00:04:37,183
Looks like her
mother has gotten better.

76
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,104
Master!

77
00:04:38,129 --> 00:04:40,298
- Ochazuke
- Ochazuke
- Ochazuke

78
00:04:41,196 --> 00:04:42,626
Coming.

79
00:04:43,727 --> 00:04:47,238
And I thought without one
they'd become a little more docile.

80
00:04:47,263 --> 00:04:48,361
Did you?

81
00:04:48,386 --> 00:04:49,716
You two over there.

82
00:04:49,866 --> 00:04:50,756
Yes?

83
00:04:50,853 --> 00:04:53,648
Don't just mumble
by yourselves, you men!

84
00:04:53,673 --> 00:04:54,293
Dammit.

85
00:04:54,426 --> 00:04:57,786
As if any of you
losers are any different.

86
00:04:58,010 --> 00:05:00,440
Bragging as if
you're anything special.

87
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:03,827
Stop talking about
yourselves alone, will you?

88
00:05:03,852 --> 00:05:09,022
All you can find at those meetings
are the leftovers, after all.

89
00:05:09,276 --> 00:05:11,626
Losers, minions and nothing else.

90
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:12,940
Right?!

91
00:05:12,965 --> 00:05:15,055
Look who's talking....

92
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:17,330
So, tell me,

93
00:05:17,585 --> 00:05:21,497
what kind of man
would you like to date?

94
00:05:21,693 --> 00:05:23,873
Someone who's
not a good for nothing,

95
00:05:24,003 --> 00:05:25,537
who spares his words,

96
00:05:25,663 --> 00:05:26,924
who has only eyes for me.

97
00:05:27,053 --> 00:05:28,358
The type who might
be popular with women,

98
00:05:28,383 --> 00:05:30,024
but can only love one.

99
00:05:30,313 --> 00:05:31,218
Like Takakura Ken?

100
00:05:31,243 --> 00:05:32,031
Right!

101
00:05:32,376 --> 00:05:34,608
Also, he must make
over 10 million yen a year,

102
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:36,993
have a house with
a garden in Setagaya.

103
00:05:37,472 --> 00:05:38,821
Also, no eldest sons!

104
00:05:38,846 --> 00:05:40,226
Since you'd have
to look after his parents.

105
00:05:40,403 --> 00:05:41,772
That's quite important...

106
00:05:41,797 --> 00:05:42,991
Right?!

107
00:05:43,016 --> 00:05:44,285
The hell is that?

108
00:05:44,350 --> 00:05:45,300
Also, a villa abroad!

109
00:05:45,628 --> 00:05:48,808
<i>About a week later...</i>

110
00:05:54,405 --> 00:05:56,028
Egg sandwich, please.

111
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:57,550
Coming.

112
00:06:04,650 --> 00:06:05,932
You know, that day?

113
00:06:05,957 --> 00:06:08,977
I was contacted for a gravure shoot!

114
00:06:09,290 --> 00:06:12,052
Although it was
just a throwaway gig.

115
00:06:12,077 --> 00:06:15,877
But it seems like eating egg
sandwich here brings me luck.

116
00:06:16,496 --> 00:06:18,541
It's just an egg sandwich.

117
00:06:22,110 --> 00:06:24,267
That guy, the other day...

118
00:06:24,292 --> 00:06:26,292
What does he do for a living?

119
00:06:27,290 --> 00:06:29,620
He should be
here soon, so wait.

120
00:06:30,410 --> 00:06:31,848
Uh? He's coming tonight?

121
00:06:31,873 --> 00:06:33,043
Yeah.

122
00:06:33,173 --> 00:06:34,853
Every night.

123
00:06:40,036 --> 00:06:40,696
Morning.

124
00:06:40,826 --> 00:06:41,678
Morning.

125
00:06:41,703 --> 00:06:44,931
Ah... Thank you for the
egg sandwich the other day!

126
00:06:45,430 --> 00:06:47,890
Ahh... It's nothing.

127
00:06:47,915 --> 00:06:51,565
If it's okay with you,
let me pay back the courtesy.

128
00:06:57,050 --> 00:06:59,170
Thank you.

129
00:07:05,997 --> 00:07:07,478
<i>That kiddo...</i>

130
00:07:07,503 --> 00:07:10,471
<i>is paying his college tuition
by delivering papers.</i>

131
00:07:10,496 --> 00:07:17,295
<i>Looks like things aren't
going well for his family.</i>

132
00:07:18,527 --> 00:07:20,268
<i>I see...</i>

133
00:07:22,495 --> 00:07:25,564
During holidays,
instead of delivering papers,

134
00:07:25,589 --> 00:07:29,139
he brings me bread,
like the other day.

135
00:07:29,993 --> 00:07:33,045
I should have given him
the whole plate, then.

136
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:35,110
He must be so hungry...

137
00:07:35,256 --> 00:07:36,576
It's all right.

138
00:07:36,676 --> 00:07:41,456
He said he always has
breakfast waiting for him at work.

139
00:08:01,883 --> 00:08:04,041
They look good together,
don't they, Master?

140
00:08:04,066 --> 00:08:06,856
Just seeing them
makes me feel elated.

141
00:08:07,023 --> 00:08:08,883
What, have you
met them before?

142
00:08:09,036 --> 00:08:12,593
The girl comes here around
the time when he delivers papers,

143
00:08:12,618 --> 00:08:15,428
and then gives
him half her egg sandwich,

144
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:17,723
while he looks
embarrassed as he takes it.

145
00:08:17,963 --> 00:08:20,893
That's so nice of her.

146
00:08:22,475 --> 00:08:26,391
So what, you're always so piss drunk
you spend the whole night here?

147
00:08:26,416 --> 00:08:28,096
Isn't it, Master?

148
00:08:28,936 --> 00:08:30,641
Now that I think
about it, you're right.

149
00:08:30,666 --> 00:08:34,551
So it's not "Midnight Restaurant,"
but the lovebirds' "Dawn Restaurant."

150
00:08:34,576 --> 00:08:37,182
Although it's okay with me.

151
00:08:37,207 --> 00:08:39,687
So he's on a scholarship...

152
00:08:39,969 --> 00:08:44,374
You rarely see students working to pay
their college fees in this day and age.

153
00:08:44,399 --> 00:08:47,189
He's quite something.

154
00:08:49,297 --> 00:08:50,574
Do you even realize...

155
00:08:50,599 --> 00:08:52,679
how hard that is?

156
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:55,135
<i>Every day,</i>

157
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:58,231
<i>you wake up at three in
the morning when it's still dark,</i>

158
00:08:58,256 --> 00:09:01,396
<i>and start delivering
papers a half hour later.</i>

159
00:09:02,126 --> 00:09:04,767
<i>By the time you're done,
it's already half past six,</i>

160
00:09:04,792 --> 00:09:08,921
<i>after which you wrap up things
at work, and head to school.</i>

161
00:09:08,946 --> 00:09:09,976
Good morning.

162
00:09:11,236 --> 00:09:14,756
<i>Then, you pay attention to your
lesson, fighting off the urge to sleep.</i>

163
00:09:18,976 --> 00:09:23,232
<i>Once the lecture is done,
you go deliver the evening papers.</i>

164
00:09:23,257 --> 00:09:25,105
<i>Even if your friends
call you out for a drink...</i>

165
00:09:25,130 --> 00:09:26,321
Nakajima,
let's have a drink.

166
00:09:26,346 --> 00:09:28,546
Sorry... Have to go...

167
00:09:28,829 --> 00:09:31,949
<i>So you can't even make friends.</i>

168
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:36,460
<i>You complete deliveries
past six in the evening,</i>

169
00:09:37,303 --> 00:09:39,352
<i>and without a minute to spare,</i>

170
00:09:39,377 --> 00:09:42,497
<i>prepare the next day's
morning papers for delivery.</i>

171
00:09:44,973 --> 00:09:46,805
And then you have to study,

172
00:09:46,830 --> 00:09:50,450
and the infernal loop starts again with
the morning papers after a little sleep.

173
00:09:50,873 --> 00:09:53,151
It's hard... Living that life...

174
00:09:53,553 --> 00:09:54,621
Kanemoto-san...

175
00:09:54,646 --> 00:09:56,682
How come you know that so well?

176
00:09:56,707 --> 00:09:58,101
Because I've experienced it firsthand.

177
00:09:58,126 --> 00:10:00,846
Ohh... You can't really judge
a book by its cover, all right.

178
00:10:01,006 --> 00:10:03,538
But after I learned this,

179
00:10:03,563 --> 00:10:06,433
I failed at both.

180
00:10:06,683 --> 00:10:09,733
Drinking is scary.

181
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:21,615
So.... That way...

182
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:22,613
Sure!

183
00:10:31,306 --> 00:10:32,199
Sorry!

184
00:10:32,224 --> 00:10:34,148
Ah... Don't worry about it!

185
00:10:34,173 --> 00:10:37,201
I should feel sorry for keeping you
on the phone for so long at that hour.

186
00:10:37,226 --> 00:10:38,696
Sorry.

187
00:10:40,437 --> 00:10:44,277
So what is this thing
you couldn't tell me on the phone?

188
00:10:48,306 --> 00:10:52,736
I was wondering what you think of me.

189
00:10:55,773 --> 00:10:58,413
That...

190
00:11:01,783 --> 00:11:04,993
I like you, Nakajima-kun.

191
00:11:09,540 --> 00:11:12,610
- I....
- Excuse me!

192
00:11:13,306 --> 00:11:15,276
Are you Aikawa Risa-san,
by any chance?

193
00:11:15,619 --> 00:11:16,068
Yes.

194
00:11:16,093 --> 00:11:18,183
It's her!

195
00:11:18,762 --> 00:11:20,226
I'm a fan!

196
00:11:20,251 --> 00:11:22,830
Ah... Thank you very much.

197
00:11:23,453 --> 00:11:24,284
I'll keep supporting you!

198
00:11:24,309 --> 00:11:25,769
Thank you.

199
00:11:25,983 --> 00:11:27,001
Keep up the good work!

200
00:11:27,026 --> 00:11:28,648
Thank you.

201
00:11:28,673 --> 00:11:30,828
- We'll keep supporting you!
- Thank you.

202
00:11:30,853 --> 00:11:34,075
- What is she doing here?
- Right? Totally awesome!

203
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,820
You still haven't answered me.

204
00:11:44,413 --> 00:11:47,451
The worlds you and I live in...

205
00:11:47,476 --> 00:11:49,816
are so different...

206
00:12:06,683 --> 00:12:09,964
That girl, she's showing up on TV
pretty often these days, isn't she?

207
00:12:09,989 --> 00:12:11,318
Seemed so.

208
00:12:11,343 --> 00:12:12,631
There's no need to worry.

209
00:12:12,656 --> 00:12:16,206
No matter how busy they are,
they'll end up together.

210
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:19,703
The world out there
isn't as easy as you think.

211
00:12:19,728 --> 00:12:21,348
Here she starts again.

212
00:12:21,373 --> 00:12:25,153
One is a up and coming talent,
the other a delivery boy.

213
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:27,395
It's not just a little difference.

214
00:12:27,420 --> 00:12:29,400
They're of a different class altogether!

215
00:12:29,693 --> 00:12:32,075
In this world of ours,

216
00:12:32,606 --> 00:12:36,075
be it the Arisu's
downstream or midstream,

217
00:12:36,813 --> 00:12:39,703
don't belittle life.

218
00:12:41,541 --> 00:12:45,959
Hepburn and Gregory Peck
will break up in the end.

219
00:12:45,998 --> 00:12:47,240
Why's that?

220
00:12:47,265 --> 00:12:51,100
<i>(*Rom-Com film starring
Audrey Hepburn and Gregory Peck)</i>
You don't know Roman Holiday*?!

221
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:52,913
What an ignorant man!

222
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:53,945
But...

223
00:12:53,970 --> 00:12:57,610
<i>(*Rom-Com films)</i>
The romance in Notting Hill* went well!
Pretty Woman*, too!

224
00:12:57,635 --> 00:13:00,042
Haha! That's funny.

225
00:13:00,808 --> 00:13:03,854
They don't even kiss, right?

226
00:13:04,615 --> 00:13:06,608
That's right...

227
00:13:06,897 --> 00:13:09,545
The voices of the two platonics
are not fulfilled.

228
00:13:09,570 --> 00:13:10,893
The price has not been decided!

229
00:13:10,918 --> 00:13:11,998
But...!

230
00:13:12,023 --> 00:13:15,740
Your heart wil cry more than your body...

231
00:13:16,365 --> 00:13:22,381
It's a loss if you are only aware of
yourself rather than your partner.

232
00:13:29,249 --> 00:13:33,282
In general... In general...

233
00:13:33,562 --> 00:13:34,869
What are you looking at?

234
00:13:36,608 --> 00:13:40,128
About Scene 19...

235
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:44,290
Give it a look before we go.

236
00:13:45,196 --> 00:13:47,693
<i>"Nakajima here, how are things?
Sorry for the other day,
can we meet again..."</i>

237
00:13:47,693 --> 00:13:49,107
<i>~ Exit? ~</i>

238
00:14:05,486 --> 00:14:07,414
<i>~ Checking Incoming Messages ~</i>

239
00:14:07,414 --> 00:14:08,801
<i>~ No Messages ~</i>

240
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,340
<i>~ Secret Late Night Meeting
Between Aikawa Risa and IT President ~</i>
<i> </i>

241
00:14:47,340 --> 00:14:50,002
<i>~ Secret Late Night Meeting
Between Aikawa Risa and IT President ~</i>
See? Just as we told you.

242
00:14:50,130 --> 00:14:52,834
See? You can't trust women.

243
00:14:52,859 --> 00:14:55,928
Losers in tears,
how miserable.

244
00:15:00,060 --> 00:15:01,650
Thank you.

245
00:15:07,036 --> 00:15:09,576
What are you
doing here,

246
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:11,670
at this hour?

247
00:15:11,706 --> 00:15:15,056
Tomorrow the paper is not coming out.

248
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:21,212
Here... Let's drink the night away.

249
00:15:21,237 --> 00:15:23,831
Women have always been
that kind of species, you know?

250
00:15:23,856 --> 00:15:26,637
Drink, go ahead.

251
00:15:26,662 --> 00:15:28,022
Thank you.

252
00:15:36,183 --> 00:15:37,461
Listen.

253
00:15:37,486 --> 00:15:38,486
What?

254
00:15:38,710 --> 00:15:40,953
Will you let these two men
enjoy their drink together?

255
00:15:41,053 --> 00:15:43,303
I'm not talking to you.

256
00:15:44,630 --> 00:15:46,770
You know?

257
00:15:46,849 --> 00:15:48,869
You're really pathetic.

258
00:15:49,643 --> 00:15:53,843
It's obvious you'd let another
man steal her under your eyes!

259
00:15:54,336 --> 00:15:55,944
If you truly
have any feelings for her,

260
00:15:55,969 --> 00:15:58,387
get her back!

261
00:15:58,679 --> 00:16:02,209
What is that pair hanging there
in the middle for, decoration?

262
00:16:18,593 --> 00:16:20,332
<i>~ Where are you? ~</i>
<i> </i>
<i> </i>

263
00:16:20,332 --> 00:16:22,048
<i>~ Where are you? ~
~ I need to meet you ~</i>
<i> </i>

264
00:16:22,048 --> 00:16:27,196
 <i>~ Where are you? ~
~ I need to meet you ~
~ and have a word ~</i>

265
00:16:28,580 --> 00:16:30,328
<i>~ Still at the studio ~</i>
<i> </i>
<i> </i>

266
00:16:30,328 --> 00:16:31,561
<i>~ Still at the studio ~</i>
<i>~ We need to talk, ~</i>
<i> </i>

267
00:16:31,561 --> 00:16:38,446
<i>~ Still at the studio ~</i>
<i>~ We need to talk, ~</i>
<i>~ I have something to say myself ~</i>

268
00:16:51,630 --> 00:16:52,735
Hey!

269
00:16:52,760 --> 00:16:54,263
Good job!

270
00:16:54,288 --> 00:16:58,302
So I hear, Risa and that
president got engaged?

271
00:16:58,327 --> 00:17:00,475
What is it? Didn't she care
about her career even a bit?

272
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:02,940
Right.

273
00:17:02,965 --> 00:17:05,128
Looks like they
were going out for real.

274
00:17:05,153 --> 00:17:08,230
She was just starting
to get noticed, it's killing me.

275
00:17:08,260 --> 00:17:10,797
Killing what...

276
00:17:27,956 --> 00:17:29,708
Risa, let's go.

277
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:34,215
I have to work early in the morning,
so I need some sleep.

278
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:11,797
Congrats.

279
00:18:12,166 --> 00:18:14,146
Thank you.

280
00:18:17,116 --> 00:18:19,837
Want some egg sandwich?

281
00:18:19,862 --> 00:18:20,862
Sure.

282
00:18:30,439 --> 00:18:35,319
We shared this the very
first day we met, didn't we?

283
00:18:48,466 --> 00:18:49,846
Yes.

284
00:18:51,243 --> 00:18:54,303
Yes, I'll come in right now.

285
00:19:00,790 --> 00:19:02,870
Thank you for that.

286
00:19:03,593 --> 00:19:06,493
So... I'll get going.

287
00:19:09,880 --> 00:19:11,720
Goodbye.

288
00:19:28,399 --> 00:19:30,070
Master...

289
00:19:30,878 --> 00:19:31,878
Yeah?

290
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:37,620
You might despise me for saying this,

291
00:19:38,019 --> 00:19:41,599
but will they eventually break up?

292
00:19:43,380 --> 00:19:45,917
When was it...

293
00:19:46,277 --> 00:19:49,277
The other day,
she came here alone.

294
00:19:52,103 --> 00:19:53,695
So...

295
00:19:54,270 --> 00:19:58,570
That president fella
finally proposed to you.

296
00:20:01,899 --> 00:20:04,429
Will you accept it?

297
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:11,780
I don't know anything about this president,

298
00:20:11,950 --> 00:20:15,580
so I can only take that kiddo's side.

299
00:20:15,730 --> 00:20:18,190
He's a decent guy.

300
00:20:20,566 --> 00:20:22,367
I know.

301
00:20:22,790 --> 00:20:25,412
I do know, but...

302
00:20:25,437 --> 00:20:32,427
Whenever I'm with Nakajima-kun,
it doesn't feel like it used to be.

303
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:43,401
He said we live in different worlds,

304
00:20:43,426 --> 00:20:44,904
and at first,

305
00:20:44,929 --> 00:20:47,935
I thought I should have told him otherwise,

306
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:52,710
but I just couldn't say a thing.

307
00:20:59,850 --> 00:21:05,060
Right when that happened,
I met this man.

308
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:07,888
I think he's a nice person,

309
00:21:07,913 --> 00:21:10,827
but I don't like him
or anything of that sort.

310
00:21:10,852 --> 00:21:13,412
That is why I talked to him
about Nakajima-kun as well.

311
00:21:14,903 --> 00:21:16,854
What did he say?

312
00:21:16,879 --> 00:21:19,452
To reflect until I can't take it anymore.

313
00:21:19,477 --> 00:21:21,023
Think and keep thinking about it,

314
00:21:21,048 --> 00:21:24,498
and if you still can't find an answer,
then it can't be helped.

315
00:21:26,076 --> 00:21:28,268
Peculiar fella.

316
00:21:29,014 --> 00:21:31,202
Thought so myself.

317
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:33,834
Still...

318
00:21:34,487 --> 00:21:37,727
He made me feel more comfortable.

319
00:21:39,530 --> 00:21:42,181
Whenever I'm with him,

320
00:21:42,206 --> 00:21:46,516
I felt I could be more sincere.

321
00:21:53,569 --> 00:21:57,779
So there's nice people
among IT presidents as well.

322
00:21:58,186 --> 00:22:00,856
As for people like me...

323
00:22:01,999 --> 00:22:04,408
She came...

324
00:22:04,433 --> 00:22:08,213
to properly bid farewell.

325
00:22:08,507 --> 00:22:12,376
Isn't falling for a woman like that...

326
00:22:12,780 --> 00:22:15,783
something you should feel proud about?

327
00:22:18,190 --> 00:22:21,968
Your feelings for her were sincere,

328
00:22:22,703 --> 00:22:26,523
so don't look down on that.

329
00:23:10,719 --> 00:23:12,295
<i>Reality...</i>

330
00:23:12,320 --> 00:23:15,840
<i>is not like what you find in the movies.</i>

331
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:24,705
<i>Nakajima-kun is still
delivering papers every day.</i>

332
00:23:24,730 --> 00:23:29,950
<i>Although I think it's still
too early for egg sandwich...</i>

333
00:23:34,646 --> 00:23:38,993
~ to be continued ~

334
00:23:39,650 --> 00:23:42,712
First things first,
finely chop the boiled egg.

335
00:23:43,090 --> 00:23:45,954
Mayo fits with just about everything,
doesn't it?

336
00:23:45,979 --> 00:23:49,445
But if you use too much,
it'll cover the taste of eggs,

337
00:23:49,470 --> 00:23:51,554
so use just enough to make
it sticky and nothing more.

338
00:23:51,579 --> 00:23:54,959
Add just the right doses
of salt and pepper.

339
00:23:55,580 --> 00:23:57,359
Ahh! Master...

340
00:23:58,417 --> 00:24:00,847
Use this for me.

341
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:05,212
So... Good night everyone!

